The paper deals with online query processing for large-scale data analysis, which is a common topic in the database (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of a distributed stream processing engine (DSPE) also suggests a potential fit with the distributed computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the handling of nested data collections, which could be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the prototype implementation of the framework on top of Spark suggests a potential fit with the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
